"Human beings who have made bad decisions still can have great potential." -@Catherine_Hoke
"The birth lottery is real. Many of us who are successful have been given great opportunities and great mentors." -@Catherine_Hoke
And on top of it all: @Catherine_Hoke is a former member of a men's wrestling team
"We love business, we're all about entrepreneurship, but we're really about lifestyle change. We're a support system." -@Catherine_Hoke
One of @DefyVentures' many great success stories: @conbodynyc/@conbodylive
Anyone who wants to get involved with @DefyVentures, even as a mentor for post-grads, can email @Catherine_Hoke at cat@defyventures.org!
"It's my vision to put @DefyVentures out of business by helping to end mass incarceration." -@Catherine_Hoke
"What would it be like if you were only known for he worst thing you've done? That became my story." -@Catherine_Hoke
"I learned I'm not the only leader who fails, and I moved back to New York City, a place I love so much." -@Catherine_Hoke
"I asked myself this dangerous little question: what if they were equipped to go legit?" -@Catherine_Hoke
"I felt sorry for how I could completely write off people and close my heart to them." -@Catherine_Hoke
"Nationally, nearly 75% of formerly-incarcerated people are re-arrested within five years." -@Catherine_Hoke
"People call what we do "second-chance work" but for many of the men and women we work with, this is a first chance." -@Catherine_Hoke
"I believe the incarcerated and formerly-incarcerated are the country's most overlooked talent pool." -@Catherine_Hoke
"Many drug dealers and gang leaders have incredible business and entrepreneurship skills." -@Catherine_Hoke
Next up: we're talking to @Catherine_Hoke, founder and CEO of @DefyVentures
